com.bluegosling.reflect

Class PackageScanner.ScanResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.reflect.PackageScanner.ScanResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Awaitable
    Enclosing class:
    PackageScanner

    public static class PackageScanner.ScanResult
extends Object
implements Awaitable
    The results of a scan. This object implements Awaitable because the results can be inspected while the scan is still concurrently running. Awaiting this result to become done will block until all path scanning operations have completed.

    Several operations are not possible until the scan operations complete. So several methods implicitly block for it to complete when invoked.

      • includesPackage

        public boolean includesPackage(String packageName)
        Determines whether the given package was encountered in this scan. If paths are still being scanned, this may block. As soon as the package is seen during one of the path scans, the method will return true. But the entire scan must complete before it will return false.
